6115H03.02H
1
2 Any individual who receives restitution under this section shall be prohibited
3 from seeking any civil redress from the state, its departments and agencies, or
4 any employee thereof, or any political subdivision or its employees. This
5 section shall not be construed as a waiver of sovereign immunity for any
6 purposes other than the restitution provided for herein. The department of
7 corrections shall determine the aggregate amount of restitution owed during a
8 fiscal year. If insufficient moneys are appropriated each fiscal year to pay
9 restitution to such persons, the department shall pay each individual who has
10 received an order awarding restitution a pro rata share of the amount
11 appropriated. Provided sufficient moneys are appropriated to the department,
12 the amounts owed to such individual shall be paid on June thirtieth of each
13 subsequent fiscal year, until such time as the restitution to the individual has
14 been paid in full. However, no individual awarded restitution under this
15 subsection shall receive more than sixty-five thousand dollars during each
16 fiscal year. No interest on unpaid restitution shall be awarded to the individual.
17 However, an individual may also be awarded other nonmonetary relief,
18 including counseling, housing assistance, and personal financial literary
19 assistance.
20 2. If the results of the DNA testing confirm the person's guilt, then the
21 person filing for DNA testing under section 547.035, shall:
22 (1) Be liable for any reasonable costs incurred when conducting the
23 DNA test, including but not limited to the cost of the test. Such costs shall be
24 determined by the court and shall be included in the findings of fact and
25 conclusions of law made by the court; and
26 (2) Be sanctioned under the provisions of section 217.262.
27 3. A petition for payment of restitution under this section may be filed
28 only by the individual determined to be actually innocent or the individual's
29 legal guardian. No claim or petition for restitution under this section may be
30 filed by the individual's heirs or assigns. An individual's right to receive
31 restitution under this section is not assignable or otherwise transferrable. The
32 state's obligation to pay restitution under this section shall cease upon the
33 individual's death. Any beneficiary designation that purports to bequeath,
34 assign, or otherwise convey the right to receive such restitution shall be void
35 and unenforceable.
36 4. An individual who is determined to be actually innocent of a crime
37 under this chapter shall automatically be granted an order of expungement
38 from the court in which he or she pled guilty or was sentenced to expunge from
39 all official records all recordations of his or her arrest, plea, trial or conviction.
40 Upon the court's granting of the order of expungement, the records and files
41 maintained in any administrative or court proceeding in an associate or circuit
42 division of the court shall be confidential and available only to the parties or by
43 order of the court for good cause shown. The effect of such order shall be to
44 restore such person to the status he or she occupied prior to such arrest, plea or
45 conviction and as if such event had never taken place. No person as to whom
46 such order has been entered shall be held thereafter under any provision of any
